quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  27,67,"Those who deny the truth say, \"When we have turned to dust like our fathers, shall we be brought back to life again"
  27,68,We and our fathers were promised this before; these are but old stories
  27,69,"Say, \"Roam across the earth and observe what was the end of the sinful ones"
  27,70,"Do not grieve over them, nor feel distressed at their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask, \"When will this promise be fulfilled, if what you say be true"
  27,72,"Say, \"It may be that a part of what you would hasten on is close behind you"
  27,73,"Truly, your Lord is bountiful to mankind, but most of them are not grateful"
  27,74,The Lord knows full well what they conceal in their hearts and what they disclose
  27,75,"there is nothing hidden in heaven and on earth, but is recorded in a clear Book"
  27,76,This Quran explains to the children of Israel much of what they differ over
  27,77,certainly it is guidance and a blessing for the believers
  27,78,"Certainly your Lord will decide between them in His wisdom, He is the Almighty, the All Knowing"
  27,79,so put your trust in God. Surely you are on the path of manifest truth
  27,80,"You cannot make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear your call, when they turn their backs on it"
  27,81,nor can you guide the blind out of their error. You can make only those hear you who believe in Our revelations and surrender themselves to Us
  27,82,"When God's word is justly carried out against them, We will produce a dabbah from the earth which will tell them that mankind had no real faith in Our signs"